WEBVTT

01:44.030 --> 01:44.863
Oh hello.

01:46.698 --> 01:47.433
Hello.

01:47.466 --> 01:48.566
Who are you?

01:51.203 --> 01:51.903
Hey!

01:52.972 --> 01:53.973
Yeah?

01:56.042 --> 01:56.942
Is this your dog?

02:00.578 --> 02:01.313
Sorry, what?

02:02.580 --> 02:03.748
Is this your dog?

02:08.154 --> 02:09.554
What?

02:09.587 --> 02:10.389
What?

02:12.091 --> 02:13.459
You're smiling.

02:13.492 --> 02:17.829
Oh, no, I didn't except
your accent to be your voice.

02:18.497 --> 02:20.399
I mean, that's all.

02:21.666 --> 02:23.202
What's wrong with it?

02:23.235 --> 02:24.003
Nothing.

02:26.338 --> 02:29.141
I was
so sad the day I met you.

02:44.622 --> 02:46.325
I can't remember why.

02:49.528 --> 02:52.431
Just stop listening.
Stop thinking.

02:53.865 --> 02:54.632
Tune it out.

02:59.038 --> 03:02.807
What's that thing you're
supposed to do? Count sheep?

03:02.841 --> 03:06.011
One sheep, two sheep,

03:06.045 --> 03:08.880
black sheep, blue sheep.

03:13.519 --> 03:14.320
Blue.

03:16.055 --> 03:18.958
I wonder if Blue ever worries.

03:18.991 --> 03:20.526
Nah.

03:20.559 --> 03:21.527
Blue doesn't worry.

03:26.999 --> 03:28.833
All these little pieces.

03:30.569 --> 03:32.871
So much to remember.

03:36.976 --> 03:39.478
That smoke smell in Jude's hair.

03:39.512 --> 03:41.313
Samantha telling
stories of the road

03:41.347 --> 03:44.550
and Ben agonizing
over the playlist.

03:47.852 --> 03:48.720
What was the song?

03:52.258 --> 03:54.393
I can't remember anymore.

03:56.595 --> 03:58.197
Focus on the important things.

04:04.170 --> 04:05.237
Jude Andrew Williams.

04:09.542 --> 04:11.377
We were married on
October 14, 2021.

04:13.078 --> 04:14.113
A Thursday.

04:33.065 --> 04:35.700
I should be writing this down.

05:03.062 --> 05:05.130
Everyone in, act like
you like each other.

05:05.164 --> 05:06.432
Pressed in tighter.

05:06.465 --> 05:08.133
Tighter, tighter, tighter.

05:08.167 --> 05:09.568
Everyone say "cliche"!

05:09.602 --> 05:11.437
Cliche!

05:11.470 --> 05:13.038
- I got you a drink.
- Oh, thank you.

05:13.072 --> 05:15.074
- Emma, get in here.
- Okay, yeah.

05:15.107 --> 05:16.408
Tim, get in!

05:16.442 --> 05:17.775
Okay.

05:21.013 --> 05:22.615
- Oh.
- Wait.

05:22.648 --> 05:23.716
One, two, three, cheese!

05:23.748 --> 05:25.750
Cheese!

05:25.783 --> 05:26.986
Thank you.

05:27.019 --> 05:28.254
- Be right back.
- Send that to me.

05:28.287 --> 05:29.288
- I'm sending it.
- Okay, good.

05:33.292 --> 05:34.660
You okay?

05:34.693 --> 05:36.894
- Yeah.
- He's bitter.

05:36.929 --> 05:40.065
Uh, I just got ahold of
work and I'll be two seconds.

05:44.270 --> 05:45.304
Hello?

05:45.337 --> 05:46.705
<i>Hey, it's Jude.</i>

05:48.840 --> 05:50.175
Are you calling me?

05:50.209 --> 05:51.277
<i>Uh, yeah.</i>

05:51.310 --> 05:52.478
<i>Why? Is this not a good time?</i>

05:52.511 --> 05:56.015
No, no, no, just that
cowards like me only text.

05:56.048 --> 05:58.284
<i>Oh, well,
well, I did text,</i>

05:58.317 --> 06:00.619
<i>but then I realized
I wasn't gonna get</i>

06:00.653 --> 06:02.354
<i>to hear that cool accent again.</i>

06:02.388 --> 06:03.589
<i>So, uh...</i>

06:03.622 --> 06:06.292
Um, um.

06:06.325 --> 06:07.693
I'm at a Halloween
party so sorry

06:07.726 --> 06:09.194
if it's a little bit loud.

06:09.228 --> 06:10.362
<i>Yeah, me too.</i>

06:10.396 --> 06:11.297
<i>How is yours?</i>

06:11.330 --> 06:12.431
Yeah, it's fine.

06:12.464 --> 06:14.199
Just a typical Halloween party.

06:14.233 --> 06:17.636
<i>Cool, well, uh you
better get back to it then.</i>

06:19.238 --> 06:20.439
Actually it's a bag of wank.

06:20.472 --> 06:21.774
<i>It's what?</i>

06:21.806 --> 06:23.142
It's just shit,
it's really shit.

06:25.877 --> 06:28.647
<i>I bet you my Halloween
party is 10 times worse.</i>

06:32.318 --> 06:33.285
Prove it.

06:34.386 --> 06:35.721
Can't it wait till tomorrow?

06:35.754 --> 06:37.122
A dog might've
been hit by a car,

06:37.156 --> 06:38.524
the details are unclear.

06:38.557 --> 06:39.458
Do you want me
to come with you?

06:39.491 --> 06:40.693
No, no, no, no, you stay here.

06:40.726 --> 06:42.328
Have fun and I'll
speak to you tomorrow.

06:46.665 --> 06:47.433
Hey!

06:49.335 --> 06:51.236
Are you George Washington?

06:51.270 --> 06:52.304
No.

06:52.338 --> 06:53.706
No, I'm Claude Bourgelat.

06:53.739 --> 06:54.973
Who's Clark Bergo...

06:55.007 --> 06:57.242
- Who's Claude-
- Come on up,

06:57.276 --> 06:58.043
I'll buzz you.

06:58.077 --> 06:59.144
Which way am I going?

06:59.178 --> 07:00.312
Just that way.

07:08.587 --> 07:12.191
Claude Bourgelat, the
French veterinary surgeon

07:12.224 --> 07:13.726
who actually opened
up the very first

07:13.759 --> 07:16.195
veterinary practices in Lyon.

07:16.228 --> 07:17.262
Lyon.

07:19.765 --> 07:21.233
Is your costume a
guy who Googles things

07:21.266 --> 07:22.534
and pretends he
already knew 'em?

07:22.568 --> 07:24.737
That is my costume.

07:25.938 --> 07:27.206
Yeah, funny, you're
actually the only

07:27.239 --> 07:28.207
person to get it right.

07:33.911 --> 07:36.715
- Shall I.. Can I?
- Yeah, come meet

07:36.749 --> 07:37.983
these clowns, come on.

07:38.984 --> 07:40.419
Welcome.

07:41.553 --> 07:42.321
Come, come.

07:46.225 --> 07:48.193
Everybody, this is Emma.

07:48.227 --> 07:49.261
Emma, this is everybody.

07:52.398 --> 07:54.099
Jude Andrew Williams.

07:54.133 --> 07:55.234
He always had a
camera in his hand

07:55.267 --> 07:57.269
and a photograph in his mind.

07:57.302 --> 07:59.271
Yeah, come on, man!

08:00.472 --> 08:02.074
He
could seem guarded at first

08:02.107 --> 08:04.576
but if you ever needed to
know how he really felt

08:04.610 --> 08:06.945
you could just look
at his pictures.

08:24.129 --> 08:28.934
It was hard to believe that
was only the beginning.

09:05.504 --> 09:06.705
Can I kiss you?

09:11.310 --> 09:12.878
I'm not available.

09:12.911 --> 09:14.880
Right. Tom.

09:14.913 --> 09:15.647
Tim.

09:15.747 --> 09:16.950
Tim.

09:16.982 --> 09:18.150
That's even worse.

09:20.652 --> 09:21.553
So, do you love him?

09:21.587 --> 09:22.387
- No.
- No?

09:23.856 --> 09:25.390
Then why are you with him?

09:25.424 --> 09:28.694
It's just what's
happening right now.

09:28.727 --> 09:29.628
Yeah, but that's not even true

09:29.661 --> 09:31.196
'cause you're here right now.

09:33.832 --> 09:36.902
I, uh, I can respect that
you're doing your thing,

09:36.936 --> 09:40.372
just take note that
I asked I guess.

09:42.407 --> 09:43.442
Noted.

09:45.945 --> 09:47.212
After you.

09:53.185 --> 09:54.887
That didn't happen!

10:19.378 --> 10:21.480
<i>It feels
wrong to make this about us.</i>

10:22.581 --> 10:23.950
<i>It's bigger than that.</i>

10:25.617 --> 10:26.418
So much bigger.

10:28.921 --> 10:30.389
We'd hear stories
from somewhere like

10:30.422 --> 10:32.558
the coast of
Maryland or Florida.

10:33.993 --> 10:36.628
Always there, not here.

10:38.163 --> 10:39.933
Like the story of the
man stranded in the ocean

10:39.966 --> 10:41.935
picked up by a fishing boat.

10:41.968 --> 10:44.202
It turned out he was
another fisherman,

10:44.236 --> 10:46.438
his boat washed up to
shore four days later.

10:47.406 --> 10:49.274
He said he couldn't
remember how to steer it

10:49.308 --> 10:50.909
so he decided to swim home.

10:54.613 --> 10:57.416
Or the woman in the marathon
who forgot to stop running.

11:04.456 --> 11:07.259
There's something quite beautiful
to these stories at first.

11:09.294 --> 11:10.964
But then a pilot
forgot how to fly.

11:15.969 --> 11:18.604
They call it NIA.

11:18.637 --> 11:20.138
Neuroinflammatory Affliction.

11:22.174 --> 11:24.776
It can affect anyone,
and there's no cure.

11:28.380 --> 11:30.616
Ben was the first person
we knew to get sick.

11:31.817 --> 11:33.785
We say get sick, but
that's not really it.

11:35.220 --> 11:39.625
Some people snap all at
once, other people fade away.

11:42.794 --> 11:45.430
I'm not really sure
which one is worse.

11:55.074 --> 11:55.841
Sup?

11:57.309 --> 11:59.045
Nothing apparently.

11:59.078 --> 12:00.145
Fell asleep.

12:32.244 --> 12:33.378
Jude?

12:33.412 --> 12:34.846
- Yeah?
- Hey, I'm going now.

12:35.681 --> 12:37.315
All right.

12:37.349 --> 12:38.517
You good?

12:38.550 --> 12:40.053
Yeah, just waking up.

12:40.086 --> 12:41.353
All right, well,
I'll see you later.

12:41.386 --> 12:42.554
- All right, babe.
- Bye, darling.

12:42.587 --> 12:43.755
Bye, bye, bye.

12:56.035 --> 12:57.602
- Hey.
- Hey.

12:57.636 --> 12:59.705
How many have we got
today? We're already packed.

12:59.738 --> 13:00.439
Just two.

13:01.640 --> 13:02.607
Come on, bud.

13:02.641 --> 13:04.177
All right, come here.

13:04.209 --> 13:05.911
I got ya, all right.

13:07.612 --> 13:08.647
Hello, you.

13:10.649 --> 13:13.418
All right, let's see if
we can find your family.

13:13.452 --> 13:14.720
Oh, yeah.

13:14.753 --> 13:15.520
Come here.

13:16.922 --> 13:18.024
- Oh, hey, I can get that.
- Oh, that's all right.

13:18.057 --> 13:19.125
- Yeah, all good.
- Oh okay.

13:19.158 --> 13:20.258
All set.

13:20.292 --> 13:21.593
- Thanks, Frank.
- Sure.

13:22.661 --> 13:23.829
Sorry, your name again?

13:26.132 --> 13:26.898
Emma.

13:26.933 --> 13:28.533
Emma, right!

13:28.567 --> 13:30.136
Right, right.

13:30.169 --> 13:33.106
Well, it's not to
uh... yeah, yeah.

14:05.138 --> 14:05.938
Jude?

14:10.275 --> 14:11.010
I thought that was you.

14:11.043 --> 14:12.744
Naps.

14:12.778 --> 14:13.845
How's it going, man? You good?

14:13.879 --> 14:15.114
Good, and you?

14:15.148 --> 14:16.015
Yeah, good
to see you man.

14:16.048 --> 14:16.782
Yeah, it's been awhile.

14:16.815 --> 14:17.682
What brings you here?

14:17.716 --> 14:18.617
I'm playing here tonight.

14:18.650 --> 14:19.986
- Here?
- Yeah.

14:20.019 --> 14:20.987
- No shit.
- Yeah.

14:22.654 --> 14:25.524
- You're still at it.
- That's right.

14:25.557 --> 14:26.625
Awesome, that's awesome.

14:26.658 --> 14:28.027
- You should come.
- Tonight?

14:28.060 --> 14:28.860
Yeah.

14:30.529 --> 14:32.430
Well, I gotta
check with my wife.

14:32.464 --> 14:34.299
- Wife?
- Yeah, I got married.

14:34.332 --> 14:35.767
Get the fuck outta here.

14:35.801 --> 14:36.668
Holy shit, man.

14:36.701 --> 14:38.670
- Man, we gotta catch up.
- Yeah.

14:38.703 --> 14:39.671
You got a minute?

14:39.704 --> 14:41.274
Yeah, I got a minute.

14:41.306 --> 14:42.340
- You need a hand or what?
- Yeah, of course, come on.

14:42.374 --> 14:43.109
- All right.
- Are you still rolling

14:43.142 --> 14:44.010
with the same crew?

14:44.043 --> 14:44.944
Yeah, I still see 'em.

14:44.977 --> 14:46.112
Yeah, yeah, yeah, what happened?

14:46.145 --> 14:47.013
Playing solo or what?

14:47.046 --> 14:48.047
Hey, man. Stop it.

14:48.080 --> 14:49.714
- What happened?
- Nothing.

16:28.580 --> 16:30.548
Coming by, sorry, sorry.

16:34.819 --> 16:36.222
- Mr. Johnson.
- Where the hell

16:36.255 --> 16:37.822
- have you been?
- Yeah, I'm so sorry, sir.

16:37.856 --> 16:39.557
You were supposed to
be here an hour ago.

16:39.591 --> 16:40.927
Yeah, I, there's
no excuse, sir.

16:40.960 --> 16:42.560
We wanted pictures of
the girls getting ready.

16:42.594 --> 16:44.763
We paid for pictures of
the girls getting ready.

16:44.796 --> 16:45.897
Yeah, I understand, I-

16:45.932 --> 16:47.934
- No, no, I don't think
you do understand.

16:47.967 --> 16:49.901
Those moments are gone,
we don't get those back.

16:49.936 --> 16:52.470
We had to get my nephew
here to take pictures.

16:52.504 --> 16:53.438
Yeah, sorry, sir.

16:54.606 --> 16:55.807
I'll get a full
deposit back to you.

16:55.840 --> 16:56.775
Hey, hey.

16:56.808 --> 16:58.411
Just take some fucking pictures.

16:58.443 --> 16:59.844
- Okay.
- Yes, sir.

17:06.953 --> 17:08.354
<i>Hi, love.</i>

17:08.387 --> 17:09.521
Hi, Mom.

17:09.554 --> 17:10.423
<i>How is it, then?</i>

17:10.455 --> 17:11.823
Yeah, fine.

17:11.856 --> 17:12.757
How was Germany?

17:12.791 --> 17:14.293
<i>Oh, didn't I tell you?</i>

17:14.327 --> 17:15.928
<i>That trip got postponed.</i>

17:15.962 --> 17:17.430
<i>I'm still at home, but I'll
be going there in a few weeks.</i>

17:17.462 --> 17:19.831
Mom, you have to
tell me these things,

17:19.864 --> 17:21.499
I'm coming to see
you in a month.

17:21.533 --> 17:22.435
- <i>Hun-</i>
- Will you be back by then?

17:22.467 --> 17:23.802
<i>I thought I did tell ya.</i>

17:24.971 --> 17:25.972
<i>Didn't I?</i>

17:26.005 --> 17:28.307
<i>But don't worry, I'll be back.</i>

17:28.341 --> 17:29.507
<i>How are ya?</i>

17:29.541 --> 17:30.875
I'm okay.

17:30.909 --> 17:33.812
Work's getting stressful,
but I'm looking forward

17:33.845 --> 17:35.047
to coming and seeing ya.

17:35.081 --> 17:36.382
I wish they hadn't
grounded all those flights

17:36.415 --> 17:39.051
so I could come sooner,
but it's all right.

17:39.085 --> 17:42.288
<i>Oh, remind me.
Is David coming with ya?</i>

17:42.321 --> 17:43.255
- Jude?
- <i>What?</i>

17:44.656 --> 17:45.958
Jude.

17:45.992 --> 17:47.326
<i>Oh, God, what did I say?</i>

17:47.360 --> 17:49.128
<i>Chris, Henry, David, Jude.</i>

17:49.161 --> 17:51.330
<i>You know I was never
good with names anyhow.</i>

17:52.999 --> 17:54.532
Yeah.

17:54.566 --> 17:58.037
Yeah, no, but it's not the first
time you've forgotten, Mom.

17:59.271 --> 18:01.240
I know I told ya I could
only get the one ticket.

18:01.273 --> 18:02.841
<i>Of course, that's right.</i>

18:02.874 --> 18:04.909
<i>Well, hug Jude for me, will ya?</i>

18:04.944 --> 18:06.012
Yeah.

18:09.914 --> 18:11.516
Mom.

18:11.549 --> 18:12.617
<i>What?</i>

18:13.918 --> 18:14.886
Are you feeling okay?

18:14.919 --> 18:16.688
<i>Yes, love. I'm great.</i>

18:17.889 --> 18:19.392
<i>You let me do the
worrying over here.</i>

18:27.866 --> 18:28.833
You all right?

18:28.867 --> 18:29.901
Yeah, you?

18:33.905 --> 18:35.941
I'm not even a vet anymore,
I'm just an executioner.

18:35.975 --> 18:36.775
I hate it.

18:38.110 --> 18:39.445
I had to put down the
most beautiful pup today,

18:39.478 --> 18:41.013
she had the most
expressive eyes.

18:41.047 --> 18:42.415
They were like human eyes.

18:44.483 --> 18:46.952
I was gonna call you and see
if I could take her home.

18:48.054 --> 18:48.820
Let's...

18:49.989 --> 18:50.855
Please let's not
get into that again.

18:50.889 --> 18:51.856
It's just one dog.

18:51.890 --> 18:53.792
No, but it's not just one.

18:53.825 --> 18:55.928
If we take one we'll
probably take 17

18:55.961 --> 18:58.431
and we already got Blue,
we don't have room.

18:59.631 --> 19:01.633
You know that we can't.

19:16.415 --> 19:17.916
What's happening?

19:21.253 --> 19:22.488
Why are you stopping?

19:25.657 --> 19:27.960
Yeah, I don't think this
bus is going anywhere.

19:31.997 --> 19:34.967
What is
happening right now?

19:36.469 --> 19:38.104
Attention.

19:38.137 --> 19:42.341
If you are lost or need
assistance, call 707

19:42.374 --> 19:44.809
and have your ID ready.

19:44.843 --> 19:47.980
If someone you know
is lost or missing,

19:48.013 --> 19:51.683
check the missing person
database or call 811

20:21.046 --> 20:23.048
Do you think anybody's immune?

20:23.082 --> 20:24.016
Oh yeah.

20:24.049 --> 20:25.551
Me, for instance.

20:25.584 --> 20:28.720
All right, so it doesn't
affect the geniuses amongst us.

20:28.753 --> 20:31.789
What if the
only person who's immune

20:31.823 --> 20:33.025
already has Alzheimers?

20:33.058 --> 20:33.825
Ooh.

20:33.858 --> 20:34.659
So you'd never know.

20:34.692 --> 20:36.529
Ooh, yeah.

20:36.562 --> 20:38.998
That is so fucked up
that's probably how it is.

20:39.031 --> 20:40.665
Or what if this is
just the next phase

20:40.698 --> 20:43.202
of human evolution and we
should just embrace it?

20:43.235 --> 20:45.004
We fucked everything up
so badly that the only way

20:45.037 --> 20:47.872
to survive this is
just by forgetting.

20:47.906 --> 20:50.708
Mm hmm, yeah,
I like that, too.

20:52.578 --> 20:53.878
What about dogs?

20:53.912 --> 20:55.314
Do you think dogs
are susceptible?

20:55.347 --> 20:56.582
Unclear.

20:56.615 --> 20:58.250
They rely more on
associative memories,

20:58.284 --> 21:00.718
so just don't change
the way you smell

21:00.752 --> 21:02.087
and keep feeding him
and you'll be fine.

21:02.121 --> 21:04.889
Hey, don't you fucking
forget about me, Blue!

21:06.559 --> 21:08.160
Oh, I'm sorry, bud.

21:08.194 --> 21:10.695
I didn't think you'd
take that so seriously.

21:10.728 --> 21:11.863
Yeah, I love you, too.

21:12.764 --> 21:14.099
Yeah, sorry, buddy.

21:17.369 --> 21:19.538
It's a shame we can't
take some of them.

21:19.572 --> 21:22.208
The dogs.

21:22.241 --> 21:24.410
They've been putting
down so many recently.

21:28.380 --> 21:29.747
What?

21:29.781 --> 21:31.749
Yeah, just like a
puppy or something.

21:32.651 --> 21:34.153
I'm sure Blue wouldn't mind.

21:36.255 --> 21:37.056
What?

21:38.624 --> 21:40.092
You said we couldn't.

21:41.293 --> 21:43.095
When?

21:43.128 --> 21:45.564
We had an argument about
this last week and then

21:45.598 --> 21:48.167
we were just about to get
into it again on the bus.

21:55.975 --> 21:56.942
Very good.

21:56.976 --> 21:58.310
- Jude, I'm-
- Almost.

21:58.344 --> 22:00.279
This is an ongoing argument
that we've been having,

22:00.312 --> 22:03.249
we were just about to get
into it half an hour ago.

22:03.282 --> 22:04.283
It was just now.

22:06.118 --> 22:08.087
I don't remember that.

22:08.120 --> 22:09.622
Oh my God.

22:14.693 --> 22:16.161
Did you know this was happening?

22:16.195 --> 22:18.664
No, how am I
gonna know I forgot?

22:18.697 --> 22:19.965
Do you know who I am?

22:19.999 --> 22:21.267
Yeah, you're my
wife, Emma Veta.

22:21.300 --> 22:22.735
Where did we meet?
